issues.title: AMG Performance Engine Harness Deterioration
issues.description: The engine wiring harness in the M157 5.5L biturbo V8 engine degrades over time, causing insulation to crack and wires to short circuit. This is particularly common near the hot engine components and can lead to complete engine failure.
issues.fix_description: Complete replacement of the engine wiring harness with updated heat-resistant materials
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of wiring harness during service, avoid excessive heat cycling

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Actuator Failure
issues.description: The electronic wastegate actuators on both turbochargers fail frequently, causing overboost or underboost conditions. The actuator motors burn out or the wastegate arms seize.
issues.fix_description: Replace wastegate actuators on both turbochargers, often requires turbo removal
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, avoid aggressive driving when engine is cold

issues.title: ABC (Active Body Control) Hydraulic Leaks
issues.description: The ABC hydraulic suspension system develops leaks in the hydraulic lines, struts, and pump. This causes the car to drop to the ground and triggers safety warnings.
issues.fix_description: Replace leaking hydraulic components, flush system, may require complete ABC system overhaul
issues.prevention: Regular ABC fluid changes, inspect for leaks during service

issues.title: COMAND Infotainment System Failure
issues.description: The COMAND head unit experiences black screen issues, freezing, and complete system failures. Often related to overheating or software corruption.
issues.fix_description: Software update, head unit replacement, or repair of internal components
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, regular software updates

issues.title: Intercooler Water Pump Failure
issues.description: The electric water pump that circulates coolant through the intercoolers fails, causing overheating and reduced turbo efficiency. Common failure point in the cooling system.
issues.fix_description: Replace intercooler water pump and thermostat, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, monitor coolant levels

issues.title: AMG Carbon Fiber Trim Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber interior trim pieces begin to delaminate and bubble, particularly on the dashboard and door panels. Purely cosmetic but expensive to repair.
issues.fix_description: Replace affected trim pieces with updated parts
issues.prevention: Avoid excessive heat and humidity, use UV protection

issues.title: Transmission Conductor Plate Failure
issues.description: The 7G-TRONIC transmission's conductor plate (valve body electrical connector) fails, causing harsh shifts, transmission slipping, and complete transmission failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace conductor plate and valve body, transmission fluid service
issues.prevention: Regular transmission service, avoid aggressive driving

issues.title: Engine Mount Deterioration
issues.description: The hydraulic engine mounts wear out prematurely due to the high torque output of the AMG engine, causing excessive vibration and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn engine mounts with updated versions
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive launches, regular inspection during service

issues.title: Brake Disc Warping
issues.description: The large AMG brake discs are prone to warping under heavy use, causing steering wheel vibration and reduced braking performance.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake discs and pads, check brake fluid condition
issues.prevention: Avoid hard braking when discs are hot, use proper cool-down procedures

issues.title: Fuel Pump Flange Leak
issues.description: The fuel pump flange develops cracks causing fuel leaks in the trunk area. This creates a fire hazard and fuel smell in the cabin.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump flange assembly and seals
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of fuel system during service

issues.title: Air Suspension Compressor Failure
issues.description: The airmatic suspension compressor overworks and fails, particularly in vehicles with ABC delete conversions or high mileage examples.
issues.fix_description: Replace air suspension compressor and check for air leaks
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of air lines and suspension components

editorial.hero_blurb: The W212 E63 AMG represents the pinnacle of sleeper sedans, delivering devastating acceleration wrapped in understated elegance. This is the car that redefined what a four-door could do.
editorial.essence: A masterclass in wolf-in-sheep's-clothing engineering, the W212 E63 AMG combines luxury sedan practicality with supercar-embarrassing performance. The 5.5L twin-turbo V8 delivers explosive power delivery that never gets old.
editorial.heritage: The E63 AMG carries forward the tradition of AMG's hand-built performance sedans, representing the last of the naturally aspirated era's transition to forced induction. This generation marked AMG's commitment to extracting maximum performance from smaller, more efficient powerplants.
editorial.design_philosophy: Understated aggression defines the W212 E63's design ethos - subtle body modifications and AMG-specific details hint at the violence beneath without screaming for attention. The goal was creating a sedan that could dominate at the track yet ferry executives in comfort.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the E63 shares DNA with AMG's touring car programs and benefits from decades of Mercedes motorsport engineering expertise in high-performance street applications.
editorial.engine_character: The M157 engine is a torque monster that hits like a freight train from low RPMs, delivering relentless surge through the midrange with a satisfying growl that builds to an aggressive roar at redline.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7G-Tronic transmission delivers lightning-quick shifts in Race mode, with perfectly calibrated downshift blips and seamless power delivery that keeps you planted in your seat.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The AMG-tuned suspension strikes an impressive balance between comfort and control, with adaptive dampers that can transform from highway cruiser to track weapon at the touch of a button.
editorial.steering_feel: Direct and communicative steering provides excellent feedback through corners, with just enough weight to inspire confidence during spirited driving while remaining effortless in daily use.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive AMG brakes deliver fade-free stopping power with excellent pedal feel, providing the confidence to fully exploit the car's considerable performance envelope.
editorial.sound_signature: A deep, menacing rumble at idle transforms into an intoxicating roar under acceleration, with turbo whooshes and aggressive pops on overrun that never fail to stir the soul.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who need four doors and a trunk, but refuse to compromise on excitement. Perfect for drivers who appreciate subtlety with their speed.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge snobs seeking obvious status symbols, eco-conscious drivers, or those prioritizing fuel economy over fury.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with full service history and avoid heavily modified cars. The M157 engine is generally reliable, but turbocharger and transmission maintenance is crucial for longevity.
